      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 B32 inline-six equipped with individual throttle bodies and a tactile 6-speed manual transmission. This example exhibits excellent mechanical health, with the double-VANOS timing system recently serviced and the rear subframe mounting points inspected for structural integrity. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from refreshed bushings and factory-spec dampening that preserves the platform's iconic 50/50 weight distribution. While the finish shows minor road patina consistent with an enthusiast-driven vehicle, the drivetrain remains robust, delivering linear power through the variable M differential lock. A purist\u2019s spec, mechanically sound and optimized for the apex.",
