      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 naturally aspirated flat-six. This example is mechanically robust, featuring a documented dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal. The 6-speed manual transaxle shifts with precision, benefiting from a short-throw kit and a healthy clutch. The suspension geometry is tight, utilizing Bilstein B6 dampers that maintain excellent damping rates through high-load cornering. Recent maintenance includes a full cooling system refresh with an LN Engineering low-temp thermostat. While the exterior shows minor stone chips and patina commensurate with high-performance use, a recent borescope inspection confirms no cylinder bore scoring. This is a driver-focused machine with linear power delivery and exceptional chassis feedback.",
